 LIBRARY ASSOCIATION/INSTITUTE OF INFORMATION SCIENTISTS SPECIAL LIBRARIESAND INFORMATION UNITS STAFFING SURVEY 1980.     THE INSTITUTE OF INFORMATION SCIENTISTS (IIS) AND THE LIBRARY ASSOCIATION (LA)CONDUCTED A JOINT STAFFING AND SALARIES SURVEY IN 1980. THIS REPLACED THE IISANNUAL REMUNERATION SURVEY AND WAS PART OF THE LA'S PROGRAMME OF SUCH STUDIES.117 QUESTIONNAIRES WERE RETURNED, EACH REPRESENTING A SPECIAL LIBRARY ORINFORMATION UNIT IN THE UK. THE RESULTS OF THE SURVEY ARE REPORTED BRIEFLY